race.comment: DIABLO LAD (3) peaks and has been racing in stronger in town. Was beaten 1L over 1200m at Belmont two back and lacked a finish over a longer sprint at Ascot last time. Comes back to 1110m today in easier company and will get every chance from the inside barrier. LUCKEE FLORAN (1) peaks off a nose defeat here this grade when he led. Presents fitter again and has more to give. Tough to peg back. FIRST CONTACT (7) turned the form around beaten 1.8L here. Will likely give away a start but should get her chance with Faithfull replacing the 3kg apprentice. SAFE HUSTLE (6) was better last time and has a low gate and 2kg claim. Stips fitter and will be around the mark.
